snippet.textDisplay: Bottled water here in the states or at least here in Vegas is a MASSIVE money maker. You would think our water coming from the tap is brown by the way they buy massive quantities of this stuff. Fact is Vegas from the tap here in Vegas is just fine, clear and clean. Coming from the East and living with well water, it was only natural I would have a filter system in place. I bought this house with its huge filtration system already in place. It came with two very large filers, one carbon and one paper. I was to change them yearly....but I didn't and it was 5 years before I did. The white paper filter was still white, not brown, not gray, but white. That is an indication the water coming into this house is VERY CLEAN. So this crazy thing about buying tons of bottled water to me makes no sense.Bottled water here in the states is a MAJOR money maker...the day I pay $6.00 for a small bottle of flavored tap water will be a cold day in hell.

snippet.textDisplay:
Where I live we have a strange relationship with tap water: 10 years ago our wells got contaminated by [redacted], an element naturally present in the rock but which concentrations grew probably because [redacted] was more active in those months.
(Sorry, it was a very local thing, I don't want to leak my location, just know that I live in Europe)
We started to not trust tap water anymore, and several effects of that are visible, but the most important one for me is that every month we go to a nearby spring to fill out tanks with potable water.
It's a tradition by now, but remember guys to never take for granted the existence of an health authority whose checks these things for you...

snippet.textDisplay: I want to take a few moments to thank you, Tom. Not only have you continued to provide interesting stories over the years (including amazing long one-take videos like this one), but you've also resisted the trend of adding background music. I just watched this entire video and my attention was held by what you were saying. Music would have distracted me and made me want to stop. I have no idea why so many people think it's a good idea, but I'm very, very glad that you don't.
